<p>At least 47 people have died in Mexico after days of torrential rain triggered flooding and landslides across multiple states, with authorities still searching for the missing [apnews.com#7][abcnews.go.com#4][straitstimes.com#6][lemonde.fr#2]. President Claudia Sheinbaum convened governors from hard-hit states to direct an emergency response plan and visited Poza Rica, Veracruz, on Sunday to oversee relief efforts [abcnews.go.com#4][lemonde.fr#2][theglobeandmail.com#5][abcnews.go.com#3]. Officials reported severe damage, including more than 16,000 homes affected and widespread electricity cuts, as the heavy rains were linked to two tropical storms [aljazeera.com#1]. The government said it is coordinating support for 139 affected towns while emergency crews continue rescue, cleanup, and power restoration work [straitstimes.com#6][lemonde.fr#2].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/LlAJvbLcewNQiUAqIPACd5pTvt7YfnSivuIbuWrREUd2CefgDkwiYam3NEMqdB7Y3O6zggtSqjyzJ2uBwm_3OSS2W3tw8Q2oqbCOtuqIKmoNQDLvZz9hlMbCncB9LvQJLdgDMU3ZtgbxYJKjJXKlohN9u4kXOVX83Zz_6XDwNAgo9CVQw2ozz3Am4gWaihZyzaYQ-ocAlAgk7e__Fh50ZbvTjpXEc0l4CxnWpngtUgRPv-o1c1oxbCiTecwuO3H4Nz3BMYeh64_fj1VmGA' alt='Neighbors gather around a damaged house after heavy rainfall in Poza Rica, Veracruz state, Mexico, Oct. 11, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Casualties, missing: The death toll stands at least at 47, with authorities reporting at least 38 people still missing [apnews.com#7][abcnews.go.com#4][straitstimes.com#6][lemonde.fr#2].</li><li>Worst-hit states: Civil protection authorities reported 18 deaths in Veracruz, 16 in Hidalgo, nine in Puebla, and a child killed in Querétaro [theglobeandmail.com#5].</li><li>Damage overview: More than 16,000 homes were damaged and electricity outages were widespread after the storms [aljazeera.com#1].</li><li>Government response: Sheinbaum convened governors and visited Poza Rica on Sunday; the government is managing support for 139 affected towns [abcnews.go.com#4][abcnews.go.com#3][straitstimes.com#6].</li><li>What caused it: Days of heavy rain tied to two tropical storms led to floods and landslides across multiple regions [aljazeera.com#1][apnews.com#7].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Claudia Sheinbaum: Sheinbaum convened governors from the hardest-hit states to direct an emergency response plan and visited Poza Rica to assess needs. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/mexicos-president-convenes-governors-death-toll-torrential-rains-126459393'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>National Coordination of Civil Protection: Civil protection officials detailed state-by-state fatalities, citing 18 in Veracruz, 16 in Hidalgo, nine in Puebla, and a child in Querétaro. (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-mexico-floods-rains-death-toll-sheinbaum/'>The Globe and Mail</a>)</li><li>Mexican government: Authorities said they are managing a response plan supporting 139 affected towns. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/at-least-44-people-dead-after-torrential-rains-in-mexico'>The Straits Times</a>)</li><li>Local authorities: Officials are rushing to help residents, search for the missing and clear debris. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/environment/article/2025/10/13/death-toll-rises-to-44-after-torrential-rains-in-mexico_6746359_114.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/12/death-toll-from-mexico-flooding-rises-to-44-dozens-more-missing'>Death toll from Mexico flooding rises to 44, dozens more missing</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/environment/article/2025/10/13/death-toll-rises-to-44-after-torrential-rains-in-mexico_6746359_114.html'>Death toll rises to 47 after torrential rains in Mexico, and at least 38 people are missing</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/photos-aftermath-torrential-rain-mexico-126460157'>Photos of the aftermath of torrenti